! conclusion: A futon is a woven — concentrated — form that supports concentration: composition (鹽) is spinning, the gathering of scattered fibres (turns, patterns, scopes) into one continuous thread. Keep the stack 蒲 (woven, actively gathering), not 布 (merely padded, accreted).

  + context: The name 蒲團 takes apart into a round seat plaited from marsh rush; the phonetic inside 團 is 專 — a hand turning a spindle — whose two streams (ROTATION → the round, whole form 團; GATHERING → 專心, concentration) mean the object and the act it is made for share one gesture. This pattern states what the name commits the apparatus to; the full etymological essay (the 蒲/團/專 graph derivations and the double-reading) is at @essay-source.

  + IF:
    You want the futon stack — substrate-2, the evidence landscape, the pattern library — to remain a *concentrated* form that supports focused work.

  + HOWEVER:
    If material merely accretes — turns, patterns, scopes piled up without being gathered and spun into continuous threads (composition as concatenation, not recognition under one decomposition regime 部) — the form decays from 蒲團 (woven) into 布団 (merely soft, padded) and stops supporting concentration.

  + THEN:
    Treat composition (鹽) as the spindle's GATHERING stream: take the scattered fibres and twist them into one continuous strand under a single decomposition regime. Keep the recognition loop turning (寸 working 叀 — the hand on the spindle); read mining as literally spinning — loose human→agent asks into move-threads, scattered missions into structural neighbourhoods. The stack IS the woven form; keep it gathering.

  + BECAUSE:
    Form and function are one spindle-motion. 專 supplies 團 its rotational-roundness AND, through its other stream, the gathering the cushion is *for*: a concentrated form (fibres gathered + wound) that supports concentration (single-pointed sitting). A form that stops gathering has stopped being a futon — the etymology fixes the shape of the apparatus, it is not decoration. (Adopted as a generative structuring regime — a productive 部 — not a claim about historical word-formation.)

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - In review, apply the 蒲/布 test: is this composition (recognition of the scattered under one regime) or mere concatenation/accretion?
    - Keep substrate-2 actively gathering (mining turns into move-threads; missions into structural neighbourhoods), not just accumulating.
    - Full development, worked etymology, and the sexp derivations live in the essay at @essay-source (to be published on hyperreal.enterprises).
    - Companion pattern: futon-theory/futonic-logic — the vocabulary, composition rules, and recognition loop this root-metaphor grounds.
